 {"id":"cass_memory_system-5eh.4","title":"cass Integration Wrapper: src/cass.ts","description":"# Feature: cass Integration Wrapper (src/cass.ts)

## Purpose
Robust wrapper around the cass CLI for searching, exporting, and managing
agent session history. Handles errors gracefully with automatic recovery.

## Functions to Implement

### Health & Availability
- `cassAvailable(cassPath)` - Check if cass is in PATH
- `cassNeedsIndex(cassPath)` - Check if index needs rebuild

### Index Management
- `cassIndex(cassPath, opts)` - Run full or incremental index rebuild

### Search
- `cassSearch(query, opts, cassPath)` - Execute search, return hits
- `safeCassSearch(query, opts, cassPath)` - With automatic error recovery

### Export & View
- `cassExport(sessionPath, format, cassPath)` - Export session to markdown/json
- `cassExpand(sessionPath, lineNum, context, cassPath)` - Get context around line

### Stats
- `cassStats(cassPath)` - Get overall cass statistics
- `cassTimeline(days, cassPath)` - Get session timeline

## Error Handling (CRITICAL)
The cass CLI has specific exit codes that we must handle:
- 0: success
- 2: usage_error (non-retryable)
- 3: index_missing (retryable: rebuild index)
- 4: not_found (non-retryable)
- 5: idempotency_mismatch (non-retryable)
- 9: unknown (non-retryable)
- 10: timeout (retryable: reduce limit)

## Implementation Details
- Use execSync for synchronous calls (simpler, avoids callback hell)
- maxBuffer: 50MB (cass can return large results)
- Default timeout: 30s per search
- Always use --robot flag for machine-readable JSON output

## Example Usage
```typescript
const hits = await safeCassSearch("authentication error", {
  limit: 10,
  days: 30,
  agent: ["claude", "cursor"]
});
